> **`wiki/` is canonical. `outputs/` is a render target.** Slides, reports, and exports are *views* of the wiki, not separate documents ‚Äî generated on demand from wiki content. The wiki is the deliverable; `outputs/` is what you ship to people who don't read wikis.

## Agent System

> **Agents are personas, not separate runtimes.** One LLM session adopts the role of whichever agent is invoked ‚Äî switching agents is switching modes (principles, checklists, capabilities), not handing off between processes. There is no inter-agent orchestration layer to worry about; the LLM simply changes hats when a launcher is run.

This wiki uses specialized agents defined in `.forge/agents/`. Each agent has
a persona, capabilities menu, and activation instructions. Activate an agent
by running its launcher from `.claude/skills/`.

